data.name: CVE-2005-3913
data.document: Unspecified vulnerability in the domain alias management in Virtual Hosting Control System (VHCS) 2.4.6.2, related to "creating and deleting forwards for domain aliases," allows users to hijack the forwardings of other users.

data.name: CVE-2005-3956
data.document: Multiple SQL injection vulnerabilities in index.php in DMANews 0.904 and 0.910 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary SQL commands via the (1) id parameter in a comments action and the (2) sortorder and (3) display_num parameters in a news_list action.

data.name: CVE-2005-3873
data.document: SQL injection vulnerability in topic.php in ShockBoard 3.0 and 4.0 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary SQL commands via the offset parameter.

data.name: CVE-2005-3977
data.document: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in QualityEBiz Quality PPC 1553 allows remote attackers to inject web script or HTML via the REQ parameter to the search module.

data.name: CVE-2005-4147
data.document: The TCLHTTPd service in Lyris ListManager before 8.9b allows remote attackers to obtain source code for arbitrary .tml (TCL) files via (1) a request with a trailing null byte (%00), which might also require (2) an authentication bypass step that involves a username with a trailing "@" characters.

references.name: 20051208 PGP Wipe Free Space, Lyris ListManager Flaws, Windows Timestamps, Sam Juicer
20051209 PGP Wipe Free Space, Lyris ListManager Flaws, Windows Timestamps, Sam Juicer

data.name: CVE-2005-2548
data.document: vlan_dev.c in the VLAN code for Linux kernel 2.6.8 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (kernel oops from null dereference) via certain UDP packets that lead to a function call with the wrong argument, as demonstrated using snmpwalk on snmpd.

data.name: CVE-2005-2612
data.document: Direct code injection vulnerability in WordPress 1.5.1.3 and earlier allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via the cache_lastpostdate[server] cookie.

data.name: CVE-2005-3891
data.document: Stack-based buffer overflow in Gadu-Gadu 7.20 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) via an image filename between exactly 192 to 200 characters, which does not account for the "imgcache\" string that is added to the end of the buffer.

data.name: CVE-2005-2829
data.document: Multiple design errors in Microsoft Internet Explorer 5.01, 5.5, and 6 allow user-assisted attackers to execute arbitrary code by (1) overlaying a malicious new window above a file download box, then (2) using a keyboard shortcut and delaying the display of the file download box until the user hits a shortcut that activates the "Run" button, aka "File Download Dialog Box Manipulation Vulnerability."

references.name: 20051213 Secunia Research: Microsoft Internet Explorer Keyboard Shortcut Processing Vulnerability
20051213 Secunia Research: Internet Explorer Suppressed "Download Dialog"Vulnerability

data.name: CVE-2005-3930
data.document: SQL injection vulnerability in index.php in N-13 News 1.2 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary SQL commands via the id parameter.

references.name: 20051129 N-13 News Remote SQL/PHP Shell injection

data.name: CVE-2005-4000
data.document: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in archive.asp in SiteBeater News System 4.00 and earlier allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via the sKeywords parameter.

data.name: CVE-2005-4077
data.document: Multiple off-by-one errors in the cURL library (libcurl) 7.11.2 through 7.15.0 allow local users to trigger a buffer overflow and cause a denial of service or bypass PHP security restrictions via certain URLs that (1) are malformed in a way that prevents a terminating null byte from being added to either a hostname or path buffer, or (2) contain a "?"  separator in the hostname portion, which causes a "/" to be prepended to the resulting string.

data.name: CVE-2005-3931
data.document: SQL injection vulnerability in default.asp in ASP-Rider 1.6 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary SQL commands via the HTTP referer.

data.name: CVE-2005-3248
data.document: Unspecified vulnerability in the X11 dissector in Ethereal 0.10.12 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (divide-by-zero) via unknown vectors.

data.name: CVE-2005-2568
data.document: Eval injection vulnerability in the template engine for SysCP 1.2.10 and earlier allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via a string containing the code within "{" and "}" (curly bracket) characters, which are processed by the PHP eval function.

references.name: 20050808 Advisory 13/2005: Remote code execution in SysCP

data.name: CVE-2005-4022
data.document: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in the "Add Image From Web" feature in Gallery 2.0 before 2.0.2 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via Javascript in an IMG tag.

data.name: CVE-2005-3331
data.document: viewpatch in mgdiff 1.0 allows local users to overwrite arbitrary files via a symlink attack on temporary files.

data.name: CVE-2005-4209
data.document: WorldClient webmail in Alt-N MDaemon 8.1.3 allows remote attackers to prevent arbitrary users from accessing their inboxes via script tags in the Subject header of an e-mail message, which prevents the user from being able to access the Inbox folder, possibly due to a cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability.

data.name: CVE-2005-3332
data.document: PHP remote file include vulnerability in admin/define.inc.php in Belchior Foundry vCard 2.9 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via the match parameter.

data.name: CVE-2005-4072
data.document: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in CFMagic Magic Forum Personal 2.5 and earlier allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via the Words parameter in search_forums.cfm, as used in the "Search For:" field.

data.name: CVE-2005-3841
data.document: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in kPlaylist 1.6 (build 400), and possibly other versions, allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via the searchfor search parameter.

data.name: CVE-2005-3923
data.document: NetObjects Fusion 9 (NOF9) allows remote attackers to obtain sensitive information, including passwords, by downloading the _versioning_repository_/rollbacklog.xml file, then using it to download and modify the associated ZIP file to edit and republish the site.
